@page "/lesson21"
<PageTitle>Parameters and Callbacks</PageTitle>

<h1>ParametersAndCallbacks</h1>

<p>
    In this lesson, you will learn how to build reusable UI components (sub component) in Blazor using Razor syntax.
    You’ll also learn how to pass data into a component using parameters
    and how to send actions back to a parent component using EventCallback.

    An event is an action the is activated by pressing button
    An attribute on the button called onclick="methodname" will cause a locate method
        to execute when the button is pressed
</p>

<p>Counter @counter</p>

<p> 
    Local button: <button @onclick="LocalButton">
        Local Button
    </button>
 
</p>

<p> 
    Using a common reusable UI component as the button
    <br/>
    <br/>
    <ActionButton Label="Add" OnClick="Increment" ButtonStyle="btn-outline-success"/>
    <ActionButton Label="Subtract" OnClick="Decrement" ButtonStyle="btn-outline-danger" />
</p>



@code {
    public int counter = 0;

    public void LocalButton()
    {
        counter++;
    }

    private void Increment()
    {
        counter++;
    }
    private void Decrement()
    {
        counter--;
    }
}
